cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.CY

The paper deals with privacy risks in IoT and focuses on the leakage of user identity through the combination of physical biometrics and device IDs. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as computer vision (cs.CV) since facial and vocal samples are used as biometrics. The paper also involves multi-modal sensing (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) since the authors propose a method to comprehensively profile victims. Finally, the paper deals with cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) since it explores the leakage of identity across both cyber and physical spaces.
